<p><i><b>Ubik</b></i> (pronounced <span title="Pronunciation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English" title="Wikipedia:IPA for English">/juːbɪk/</a></span> "yoo-bik"<sup id="cite_ref-Hour25_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Hour25-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>) is a <a href="/wiki/1969_in_literature" title="1969 in literature">1969</a> <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> <a href="/wiki/Novel" title="Novel">novel</a> by <a href="/wiki/Philip_K._Dick" title="Philip K. Dick">Philip K. Dick</a>. In 2005, <i><a href="/wiki/Time_(magazine)" title="Time (magazine)">Time</a></i> named it one of the one hundred greatest English-language novels published since 1923.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
